<html><head><title>The Town Hall Conservative Current</title></head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/thcc/images/background.gif">
<table border="0">
<tr>
<td width="100">
</td>
<td width="400">

<ul>
<img src="/thcc/thcc-logo.gif" alt="The Town Hall Conservative Current"><P>
</ul>
<center><h4><a href="/thcc/sample.html.cgi">Click here if you are not yet a subscriber</a></h4></center>
<blockquote>
<center>
<b>The Week in Review</b><br>
<i>The last week's columns</i>


</center><p>
<a href="/thcc/content/bozell/boze011097.html"><img src="/thcc/images/bozell.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="L. BRENT BOZELL">
<b>"THE PEOPLE VS. LARRY FLYNT": GROSS</b></a><br>

"The People Vs. Larry Flynt" opens with a scene set in rural Kentucky 45 years ago. The title character,
     age 9 or so at the time, and his slightly younger brother run a moonshining operation.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/chapman/chap011097.html"><img src="/thcc/images/chapman.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="STEPHEN CHAPMAN">
<b>A CLOUDY CUBA PICTURE? DON'T ADJUST YOUR SET</b></a><br>

The prevailing wisdom is that on matters of foreign policy, Bill Clinton has grown considerably in the last
     four years.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/fields/fiel011097.html"><img src="/thcc/images/fields.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="Suzanne Fields">
<b>THE INSECURITY OF SOCIAL SECURITY</b></a><br>

My daddy was a gambling man and proud of every penny he earned. He was proud of his alma
     mater -- the College of Hard Knocks -- where tuition for learning the ropes cost considerably more than
     tuition in the classics. 
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/greenberg/gree011097.html"><img src="/thcc/images/greenberg.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="Paul Greenberg">
<b>POLITICS AND SAUSAGE</b></a><br>

Everybody knows how politics usually works, just as folks understand something about how
     sausage is made. But who would relish taking a close look? 
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/huffington/huff011097.html"><img src="/thcc/images/huffington.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="ARIANNA HUFFINGTON">
<b>PROFILES IN COURAGE</b></a><br>



     So what happens if you are one of the nine Republicans who refused to vote for the newly re-elected
     speaker? For starters, you are sent to bed without dinner.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/novak/nova011097.html"><img src="/thcc/images/novak.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="ROBERT D. NOVAK">
<b>NEWT'S RIGHT-WING DISSENTERS</b></a><br>

After absentee ballots saved her from seemingly certain defeat in her heavily
     Democratic Washington state district, Republican Rep. Linda Smith conversed with Rep. John Kasich.
<p><br>

<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/sowell/sowe011097.html"><img src="/thcc/images/sowell.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="THOMAS SOWELL">
<b>THE SOCIAL SECURITY PYRAMID</b></a><br>

A recent letter from an elderly lady living on Social Security reacts to a growing impression that people
     like her are "a drag on society" and closed: "We don't ask to live this long." 
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/thomas/thom011097.html"><img src="/thcc/images/thomas.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="Cal Thomas">
<b>KILLING US SOFTLY WITH THEIR SONG</b></a><br>

How appropriate that in the 24th-anniversary month of Roe vs. Wade, which denied the right to life
     to an unborn baby, the U.S. Subc-thomaourt has heard arguments on whether individuals have a
     constitutional ``right to die.'' 
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/toledano/tole011097.html"><img src="/thcc/images/toledano.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="RALPH de TOLEDANO">
<b>GULAG AND THE LATE-DETERMINED BLINDNESS OF THE MEDIA</b></a><br>

In a recent column, New York Times columnist William Safire credits Alexander Solzhenitsyn for making
     famous the term "gulag," the acronym for the Soviet slave-labor camps and for giving us a kind of
     overhead view of a Russian map dotted with those centers of horror and inhumanity.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/tyrrell/tyrr011097.html"><img src="/thcc/images/tyrrell.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="R. EMMETT TYRRELL JR.">
<b>PUBLIC NUISANCES</b></a><br>

One of the great clowns of American politics has just sounded off! And who might that be? So many
     come to mind. Well, I have in mind no lesser a buffoon than former Speaker of the House Jim Wright, in
     all his periphrastic absurdity.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/fields/fiel010997.html"><img src="/thcc/images/fields.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="Suzanne Fields">
<b>WHEN MARRIAGE IS THE FOOD OF LOVE</b></a><br>

Forget those college courses in Women's Studies and learned seminars in Men's Studies. How
     about some book learning in the study of love and marriage? 
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/greenberg/gree010997.html"><img src="/thcc/images/greenberg.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="Paul Greenberg">
<b>THE SHOCKING TRUTH ABOUT IKE</b></a><br>

While the Nixon archives were revealing their usual layers of sleaze, something shocking did go on
     display at the National Archives last week. It was the statement General Dwight Eisenhower wrote on a
     slip of paper June 5, 1944, folded-up, put in his wallet, and never had to release.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/thomas/thom010997.html"><img src="/thcc/images/thomas.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="Cal Thomas">
<b>WILL THE NEXT BRITISH ELECTION BE A REPLAY OF THE LAST AMERICAN ONE?</b></a><br>

The coming British election, which must be held no later than May, is shaping up as a
     nasty brawl. The new Labor Party leader, Tony Blair, hopes to topple 17 years of Conservative Party
     power by knocking out Prime Minister John Major. 
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/williams/will010997.html"><img src="/thcc/images/williams.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="Armstrong Williams">
<b>PORTRAIT OF A COMMENTATOR</b></a><br>

My views are sometimes considered controversial or out of the ordinary, and many read my
     columns expecting to have their assumptions and opinions challenged. As a new year dawns, let me take
     an opportunity to explain my perspective and share with readers what aspects of my life shape that
     perspective.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/feder/fede010897.html"><img src="/thcc/images/feder.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="DON FEDER">
<b>HOLLYWOOD'S FEMINIST MESSAGE</b></a><br>"Evita" (don't you just love musicals about fascist babes who sleep their way to the top?) isn't the only
     dumbness in the movies these days.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/greenberg/gree010897.html"><img src="/thcc/images/greenberg.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="Paul Greenberg">
<b>LETTER TO AN IRATE READER -- AND FRIEND</b></a><br>Dear irate reader and friend, 

         It was wholly a pleasure to hear from you, as it always is. You needn't have been concerned about
     my not wanting to speak to you again after reading your opinion of my columns during the late
     unpleasantness and election.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/saunders/saun010897.html"><img src="/thcc/images/saunders.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="DEBRA J. SAUNDERS">
<b>YOU'RE ENTITLED TO IT -- OR WHAT'S LEFT OF IT</b></a><br>Before the Social Security advisory committee on which he serves released its report yesterday, former
     Social Security commissioner Robert M. Ball lamented to The New York Times that the surge of interest
     in privatizing Social Security represented a betrayal of "community solidarity." 
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/bowles/bowl010797.html"><img src="/thcc/images/bowles.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="LINDA BOWLES">
<b>GET A BACKBONE</b></a><br>In contrast to many of the scandals in our nation's capital involving you-know-who, the facts of Newt
     Gingrich's ethics problems are fairly simple.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/chapman/chap010797.html"><img src="/thcc/images/chapman.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="STEPHEN CHAPMAN">
<b>THE "RIGHT TO DIE": WHERE WILL IT LEAD?</b></a><br>
     When the Supreme Court convenes Wednesday, it will be asked to rule that the Constitution protects the
     right of fatally ill patients who fear a painful death to hasten the inevitable with the help of a physician.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/greenberg/gree010797.html"><img src="/thcc/images/greenberg.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="Paul Greenberg">
<b>HOW MANY CAN YOU IDENTIFY? 1996 IN 60 SECONDS</b></a><br>``The era of big government is over.'' Steve Forbes. Dixville Notch. Phil Gramm. Comet
     Hyakutake. Pat Buchanan. Greg Norman. Stocks higher. Unabomber. Chechnya. Bosnia. The Khobar
     Towers in Dharan. Northern Ireland. Yasser Arafat and Benjamin Netanyahu. Colin Powell. Bob Dole.
     Jack Kemp. Kevorkianism. Al Gore and Lamar Alexander. Hillary Clinton and Eleanor Roosevelt. 
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/huffington/huff010797.html"><img src="/thcc/images/huffington.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="ARIANNA HUFFINGTON">
<b>DRIVE-BY POLITICS</b></a><br>
     When Congress passed the 48-hour maternity bill last year, conservatives warned that the new law was
     the first step down the slippery slope of micromanaging health care, one ailment at a time. The 105th
     Congress has barely begun, and the critics are already being proved right.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/murchison/murc010797.html"><img src="/thcc/images/murchison.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="WILLIAM MURCHISON">
<b>MAIN STREET U.S.A.</b></a><br>While the House and the media meditate over whether to lynch Newt Gingrich, the Supreme Court takes
     up a graver question: whether to legitimize procedures deadlier than the Capitol Hill set has devised.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/novak/nova010797.html"><img src="/thcc/images/novak.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="ROBERT D. NOVAK">
<b>REVIVING TAX REFORM</b></a><br>Republican Rep. Bill Archer, chairman of the House Ways and Means Committee,
     was not expecting much when he entered the Oval Office Dec. 27 for a requested private meeting with
     President Clinton. He left 70 minutes later a totally startled man, hope restored that his dream of radical
     tax reform might yet be achieved before he leaves Congress four years hence.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/feder/fede010697.html"><img src="/thcc/images/feder.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="DON FEDER">
<b>AIR GUNS, INFANTICIDE AND ABORTION'S DEMENTED DOGMA</b></a><br>Last week, a Canadian court dismissed charges against an Ontario woman who chose to exercise control
     of her body by putting a pellet from an air gun in the brain of her unborn child. 
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/fields/fiel010697.html"><img src="/thcc/images/fields.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="SUZANNE FIELDS">
<b>AN EBONICS PLAGUE ON RACE RELATIONS</b></a><br>Ebonics has not been helpful to race relations. It brings out the worst thoughts if not the worst
     words from both black and white. Whites who defend ebonics as a second language, or even a place for
     it in the classroom, sound patronizing and condescending. 
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/greenberg/gree010697.html"><img src="/thcc/images/greenberg.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="Paul Greenberg">
<b>EBONICS</b></a><br>Today's lesson: You dis somebody's language, you be in trouble. 
 
         This caveat needs to be kept in mind as a national debate with a lot more heat than light erupts out
     of Oakland, Calif., where a school board seeking the usual federal grant set out to get one for the study of
     something called Ebonics.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/novak/nova010697.html"><img src="/thcc/images/novak.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="ROBERT NOVAK">
<b>INSIDE REPORT</b></a><br>Rep. Linda Smith, who clashed with Newt Gingrich over campaign finance reform as
     a freshman Republican in the 104th Congress, could end up voting against his re-election as speaker of
     the House.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/snow/snow010697.html"><img src="/thcc/images/snow.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="TONY SNOW">
<b>THE SEARCH FOR TRUTH</b></a><br>Scandal has crept upon the U.S. Capitol on little cat's feet. The "mindless
     cannibalism" Jim Wright prophesied nearly eight years ago has arrived: Democrats are turning
     Gingrich-bashing into an Olympic sport, and Republicans are preparing to conduct Torquemada-like
     inquisitions of Richard Gephardt, David Bonior, Bill Clinton, Hillary Rodham Clinton and anybody who
     has purchased so much as a frozen yogurt in the state of Arkansas. 
<p><br>




</blockquote>









<ul>
<i>The contents of this forum are copyrighted by the specified source and may not be forwarded, published, broadcast, rewritten or otherwise distributed without the prior written authority of the specified copyright owner.
</i>
</ul>
