<tr><td width="200"><td width="340"><P>

<H3><CENTER>C-News Info</CENTER></H3>


    C-News is a mailing list dedicated to providing conservatives on the 'net with a reliable source of conservative news and opinions. C-News is not a discussion list; rather, it is a "moderated" list, which means that no message makes it to the list members unless it has been approved by the list editor.<P>
    Messages from C-News cover a wide variety of materials, from Republican National Committee press releases, to Laissez Faire Book Reviews.  There's a <A HREF="/cnews/example.html">sample issue</A> of C-News on this server to give you an idea of what information you can obtain through C-News.<P>
    The traffic on C-News averages 8 to 10 messages per weekday, totalling around 50K-80K in total size.  No messages are sent to the list on weekends.<P>  
    Still interested? Then go ahead and <A HREF="/cnews/subscribe.html">subscribe</A>.  To submit a message to C-News, e-mail it to c-news@world.std.com.  If your message meets the list <A HREF="/cnews/policy.html">standards</A> and is approved by the editor, it will be sent on to the list members.<P>

