<Center><h2>Latest Republican Outrage</h2></center><p>

<hr size="4" width ="40%">
<br>
<br>
<font size="+2"><B>May 7, 1996:</b></font><P>
<ul>Health Care Reform grinds to a halt because Liberal GOP Senators Hatfield, Bond, Gorton, Chafee, Gorton and Kassebaum fail to support <a href="/conservative/lout0507.html">Medical Saving Accounts.</a></ul><P> 
<font size="+2"><B>February 28, 1996:</B></font>  
<ul>Senators Chafee and Specter have refused to vote against the Democrat filibuster of the <a href="lout0228.html">District of Columbia's approprations bill</a>, which includes a school choice (vouchers) pilot program.
</ul><P>
<hr width="30%">
<P>

<b>Past Outrages:</b>
<ul>
<li>Republican congressional leaders announced that
 <a href="/conservative/lout1223.html">furloughed federal employees will be paid</a> for time
missed due to the shutdown -- despite the fact that many are using their 
time off to fit in last-minute Christmas shopping.
<li><a href="out1024.html">Certain Senators</a> make it easier for President Clinton to send troops as he pleases
<li><a href ="spectern.html">Arlen Specter strips Labor-Health and Human Services appropriations bill</a> of tough legislative riders that were attached in the House<br>
