Women's Action Alliance<SUP>3</SUP>			$5,000
Women's Legal Defense Fund<SUP>3</SUP>			$16,000
</pre>
<P>
<I>Source</I>: American Express failed to respond to repeated written requests for information.  By telephone on April 7, 1994 and again by telephone on May 18, 1994, a company representative requested another copy of the initial request and indicated that a response was forthcoming.  By mail received July 11, 1994, American Express Foundation representative Mary Beth Salerno provided grant recipients lists for both the foundation and direct corporate contributions.  The list of foundation grant recipients, however, did not include the dollar amounts of the grants awarded.  These were provided on the American Express Foundation's 1992 990-PF, which was obtained from the Foundation Center.  The giving pattern for American Express, then, is derived from all of the requested information.
</small></UL><P>
<P>



