<P>
Re: Vol. I, no.4 article on Opera.
[&quot;Why did a reclusive widow give the Washington Opera eighteen
million dollars?&quot; <I>Culture Watch</I>] &quot;The example
of the Washington Opera has given the lie to NEA lobbyists who
claim cutting federal funding of the arts will undermine the survival
of art itself.&quot; 
<P>
Seems an odd place to find anti-NEA
sentiments. 
<P>
There is no question that the very
modest support USA has given to support of the Arts through NEA
has contributed to a growth in the arts especially dance and perhaps
Opera too etc. 
<P>
The pittance given has never been the
main support of any organization, in an era of high crime it seems
crazy to cut back on arts support.
<P>
One toilet didn't kill defense. Does
a bad grant kill the NEA?
<P>
Why not support the arts?  It beats
welfare for the defense contractors.
<P>
Mary H.D. Swift
<P>
